Well. It would have been! If you were skeptical about the value of your gia=
nt stash of crypto, you wouldn=E2=80=99t borrow customer money against it, =
and you wouldn=E2=80=99t keep spending real money on endorsements and donat=
ions. You=E2=80=99d only do that if (1) you were naively optimistic about t=
he value of your crypto or (2) you were=C2=A0extremely=C2=A0cynical, and st=
ealing it.
The defense is that Bankman-Fried was incredibly naive. It not only require=
s you to believe=C2=A0that his=C2=A0lieutenants were stealing all the custo=
mer money without him noticing, that he made a series of innocent risk mana=
