r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  which Bankman-Fried once =
expressed to me on a podcast</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0that you can just make up a=
 cryptocurrency, ascribe to it some arbitrary market value, and then borrow=
 millions of dollars against its fake market value.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Three: The facts are still unclear, and my ass=
umption is that the vast majority of the $8 billion-ish of missing customer=
 money went to Alameda, which lost it on dumb crypto bets.<a class=3D"footn=
ote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: n=
one !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bor=
der-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important=
; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0But not all of it! Lewis says on=C2=A0<em>60 Minutes=C2=A0</em>th=
at Tom Brady got paid $55 million for endorsing FTX, and he was one of many=
 highly paid celebrity endorsers. There were many millions of dollars spent=
 on political donations and effective altruism stuff and Bahamas real estat=
e and the profligate operations of FTX.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could imagine some sort of accounting in w=
hich all of those expenses were rigorously paid for out of FTX=E2=80=99s op=
erating income (from fees it legitimately charged customers for trading, an=
d that they paid in cash), while the $8 billion was lost entirely due to=C2=
=A0unfortunate mistakes in Alameda=E2=80=99s leverage. But there=E2=80=99s =
no suggestion that any accounting like that=C2=A0<em>exists</em>, and every=
one agrees that FTX=E2=80=99s actual accounting was cartoonishly bad. (=E2=
=80=9CFor example, employees of the FTX Group submitted payment requests th=
rough an on-line =E2=80=98chat=E2=80=99 platform where a disparate group of=
 supervisors approved disbursements by responding with personalized emojis,=
=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32899702=
.261426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTE=
tMTcvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1mdHgtd2FzLW5vdC12ZXJ5LWNhcmVmdWw_Y2=
1waWQ9QkJEMTAwMjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld=
3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMDAyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4=
